# Documentation maintenance

Documentation is **part of done**. Update in the same commit/PR as the change.

| You changed… | Update |
|---|---|
| Feature scope, limits, UX flow | `docs/PROJECT.md` |
| Tables, services, sync, env vars | `docs/ARCHITECTURE.md` |
| Completed or new roadmap task | `docs/ROADMAP.md` |
| Chose between alternatives (why X) | `docs/DECISIONS.md` (append, dated) |
| Setup commands or scripts | `README.md` |
| Agent workflow or reading order | `AGENTS.md` |

## Decision log entry template

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Title
**Context:** …
**Decision:** …
**Consequences:** …
```

Never delete old decisions — add a new entry that **Supersedes** the old one.

## Roadmap updates

Change task status: `⬜` → `✅` and add completion date where applicable.

## Do not create

- Extra markdown files unless the user asks or a doc above needs a new major section
- Duplicate info across files — link between docs instead
